28:49.635 --> 28:56.763
I'd give him an answer on Saturday. On Friday, They 
reorganized the old tech service division and

28:58.223 --> 29:05.856
reorganized the whole refining operation. They 
split off chemicals from petroleum, where we made

29:06.858 --> 29:15.894
two separate entities, had a chemical plant 
manager and a refinery manager. And I was given the

29:16.715 --> 29:23.387
job of technical superintendent for chemicals.

29:23.907 --> 29:26.690
So I called Mason up to talk to him. I decided I was 
going to accept the job. I called him up and he said,

29:28.532 --> 29:37.402
I withdraw my offer.

29:37.842 --> 29:40.385
He said, you're going to stay. That's what he told 
